AT THE COFFEE SHOP

302
00:22:32,633 --> 00:22:34,100
WATCHING THE SKATE SQUAD
ABUSE THEIR NUTS.

303
00:22:34,133 --> 00:22:36,800
CAN YOU THINK OF ANYTHING
SUCKIER?

304
00:22:36,833 --> 00:22:38,933
- WE COULD GO HANG OUT
IN MY COUSIN'S BASEMENT.

305
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:42,633
- MOLLY, I WASN'T ACTUALLY
ASKING FOR SUGGESTIONS.

306
00:22:42,667 --> 00:22:45,167
- I LIKE IT HERE.

307
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:48,133
- KAY, THIS WHOLE CRUSHING
FROM AFAR THING IS PATHETIC.

308
00:22:48,167 --> 00:22:50,900
AT LEAST GIVE THE GUY A HANDY,
LET HIM KNOW YOU'RE INTERESTED.

309
00:22:50,933 --> 00:22:53,133
- OH, SHUT UP ZOE.
- LOOK, I'M JUST SAYING

310
00:22:53,167 --> 00:22:54,733
IF YOU DON'T HOOK UP WITH HIM
THIS WEEKEND,

311
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:57,167
SOMEBODY ELSE WILL.

312
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:59,500
MAYBE EVEN MOLLY.
- YEAH, MAYBE I WILL.

313
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:01,133
WHY NOT?

314
00:23:01,167 --> 00:23:03,567
- YOU'RE SUCH A SLUT!

315
00:23:06,333 --> 00:23:08,233
- THAT'S SKYE.

316
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:12,867
- OH, MY GOD.

317
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:14,067
THAT'S HER?

318
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:15,700
- WHO?

319
00:23:15,733 --> 00:23:16,967
- YEP, THAT'S HER.

320
00:23:17,067 --> 00:23:20,067
- ARE YOU GOING TO
INTRODUCE US?

321
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:25,333
- HEY, YOU MUST BE SKYE.
I'M ZOE.

322
00:23:25,367 --> 00:23:29,067
- UH, HEY.
UH, I WAS ACTUALLY JUST LEAVING.

323
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:31,067
- NO, STICK AROUND.

324
00:23:31,067 --> 00:23:34,567
ANY HALF-SISTER OF ALEX
IS A HALF-FRIEND OF MINE.

325
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:36,400
- ARE YOU LIKE ADOPTED
OR SOMETHING?

326
00:23:36,433 --> 00:23:38,900
- YEAH, UH, YOU KNOW,
THAT'S OKAY.

327
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:40,633
YOU GUYS HANG OUT.

328
00:23:40,667 --> 00:23:43,200
- NO.
STAY.

329
00:23:51,733 --> 00:23:56,067
- HEY, JAMS,
ALEX SURE IS LOOKING FORWARD

330
00:23:56,067 --> 00:23:58,300
TO YOUR PARTY ON FRIDAY.

331
00:23:58,333 --> 00:23:59,733
- SORRY TO DISAPPOINT LADIES,

332
00:23:59,767 --> 00:24:01,733
BUT THE FESTIVITIES
ARE NOT HAPPENING.

333
00:24:01,767 --> 00:24:04,733
MY PARENTS ARE GOING TO BE HOME
ALL WEEKEND.

334
00:24:04,767 --> 00:24:06,800
- YOU SUCK.

335
00:24:06,833 --> 00:24:09,100
WHAT DID YOU DO FOR FUN
BACK HOME, SKYE?

336
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:15,267
- UM, JUST...YOU KNOW...

337
00:24:16,267 --> 00:24:20,233
- NO, NOT REALLY.

338
00:24:20,267 --> 00:24:22,100
BUT OKAY.

339
00:24:22,133 --> 00:24:25,533
- THERE HAS TO BE SOMEWHERE
WE CAN KICK IT, RIGHT?

340
00:24:25,567 --> 00:24:30,133
- WISH MY DAD'S CLUB WAS OPEN.
WE COULD GO THERE.

341
00:24:30,167 --> 00:24:31,567
- WELL, WHY CAN'T WE?

342
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:35,067
- BECAUSE IT'S NOT OPEN.

343
00:24:35,067 --> 00:24:36,533
IT'S LIKE AN ABANDONED
BUILDING.

344
00:24:36,567 --> 00:24:38,100
- THAT'S PERFECT.

345
00:24:38,133 --> 00:24:39,767
WE'LL JUST TAKE THE KEYS,
WE'LL THROW THE PARTY THERE.

346
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:41,100
- ZOE, I CAN'T.

347
00:24:41,133 --> 00:24:43,600
- YES, YOU CAN.

348
00:24:43,633 --> 00:24:46,133
- YOU KNOW, YOU DON'T HAVE TO
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO.

349
00:24:46,167 --> 00:24:47,900
- NO, SHE WANTS TO.

350
00:24:47,933 --> 00:24:50,500
SHE JUST NEEDS A LITTLE
ENCOURAGEMENT FROM FRIENDS.

351
00:24:50,533 --> 00:24:51,900
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE FOR.

352
00:24:51,933 --> 00:24:54,400
- ALEX, THAT WOULD BE DOPE.

353
00:24:54,433 --> 00:24:58,233
YOU PROVIDE THE SPACE,
I'LL PROVIDE THE JAMS.

354
00:24:59,433 --> 00:25:01,067
- EW.

355
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:07,767
- I'VE GOTTA GO.
MY DAD'S LEAVING LATE.

356
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:10,933
- AH, I'LL GIVE YOU A RIDE.

357
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:13,167
- THANK YOU.

358
00:25:14,833 --> 00:25:16,367
- NICE TO MEET YOU SKYE.

359
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:18,600
- YEAH.
YOU TOO.

360
00:25:19,933 --> 00:25:22,133
- SHE'S NOT GOING TO DO IT.
- WE'LL SEE.

361
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,700
BYE.

362
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:37,333
- SHE KNEW YOU WERE LEAVING.
SHE SAID SHE WOULD BE HERE.

363
00:25:37,367 --> 00:25:41,600
- THAT'S FINE.
I GOTTA GET GOING.

364
00:25:41,633 --> 00:25:44,367
FIGURE I'D STOP BY THE CLUB
BEFORE THE FLIGHT.

365
00:25:49,833 --> 00:25:52,933
YOU GOING TO BE OKAY HERE?

366
00:25:54,567 --> 00:25:56,833
- I WILL BE OKAY.
- OKAY.

367
00:25:56,867 --> 00:25:58,167
- OKAY.

368
00:26:12,933 --> 00:26:15,300
[vehicle approaches]

369
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:20,867
- SORRY WE'RE LATE.

370
00:26:20,900 --> 00:26:23,067
- YOU MISSED YOUR DAD.

371
00:26:23,067 --> 00:26:24,367
YOU KNOW HE'S REALLY
STRESSED RIGHT NOW,

372
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:25,600
AND I DON'T THINK
IT'S TOO MUCH TO ASK

373
00:26:25,633 --> 00:26:28,067
FOR YOU TO BE HERE
WHEN HE LEAVES ON A TRIP.

374
00:26:28,067 --> 00:26:30,100
- I SAID I'M SORRY.

375
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:34,367
SHE HATES IT WHEN HE TRAVELS,
SO SHE TAKES IT OUT ON ME.

376
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:37,700
PARENTS CAN BE SO MESSED UP.

377
00:26:37,733 --> 00:26:39,200
GUESS YOU KNOW THAT.

378
00:26:39,233 --> 00:26:42,533
YOUR DAD MUST BE A NIGHTMARE
TO END UP HERE.

379
00:26:42,567 --> 00:26:45,367
- MY DAD'S DEAD.

380
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:48,433
- I'M SORRY, I DIDN'T KNOW.

381
00:26:48,467 --> 00:26:53,233
- * YOU BRING SUNSHINE

382
00:26:53,267 --> 00:26:56,333
[volume rises]
* WHEN YOU'RE WALKIN' THROUGH

383
00:26:56,367 --> 00:26:59,500
*

384
00:26:59,533 --> 00:27:04,333
* AND EVERYTHING
FEELS RIGHT *

385
00:27:04,367 --> 00:27:06,767
* WHEN YOU'RE JUST BEIN' YOU

386
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:08,967
[cell phone rings]

387
00:27:09,067 --> 00:27:11,433
- HELLO.

388
00:27:11,467 --> 00:27:13,433
YEAH, I'M ON MY WAY.

389
00:27:13,467 --> 00:27:15,900
YEAH, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

390
00:27:15,933 --> 00:27:17,767
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

391
00:27:21,067 --> 00:27:24,500
- * WE'VE GOT ALL WE NEED

392
00:27:24,533 --> 00:27:25,667
* RIGHT HERE

393
00:27:25,700 --> 00:27:28,133
- UH-HUH.

394
00:27:28,167 --> 00:27:30,933
YEAH.

395
00:27:30,967 --> 00:27:33,667
YEAH, PETE, THEY'RE RUNNING
A LITTLE BEHIND.

396
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:36,633
YEAH, WE'RE WAITING ON
FINAL APPROVAL ANYWAYS.

397
00:27:36,667 --> 00:27:38,267
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?

398
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:40,600
OKAY, NO, I'LL DEAL WITH IT
WHEN I GET BACK.

399
00:27:40,633 --> 00:27:42,333
GREAT.
THANKS.

400
00:27:53,100 --> 00:27:54,667
- PARDON ME.

401
00:27:54,700 --> 00:27:57,233
MY DARN TRUCK WON'T START.

402
00:27:57,267 --> 00:28:00,700
I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU HAD JUMPER CABLES.

403
00:28:00,733 --> 00:28:02,467
- UH...

404
00:28:02,500 --> 00:28:04,233
YEAH, YEAH SURE.

405
00:28:04,267 --> 00:28:07,133
COME ON.

406
00:28:07,167 --> 00:28:08,700
BUMMER, HUH?

407
00:28:13,767 --> 00:28:16,067
GET THIS OUTTA HERE.

408
00:28:16,067 --> 00:28:19,067
- YOU KNOW, YOU...
YOU LOOK REALLY FAMILIAR.

409
00:28:19,067 --> 00:28:20,833
- EH, IT'S A SMALL TOWN.

410
00:28:20,867 --> 00:28:22,633
YOU LIVE AROUND HERE?

411
00:28:22,667 --> 00:28:26,167
- NAH, MY DAUGHTER'S HERE
STAYING WITH HER MOM,

412
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:27,833
BUT I CAME
TO BRING HER HOME.

413
00:28:27,867 --> 00:28:29,733
- OH, THAT'S NICE.

414
00:28:29,767 --> 00:28:34,067
- YOU GOT KIDS?
- YEAH, A DAUGHTER, ACTUALLY.

415
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:36,067
- I BET YOU GIVE HER
EVERYTHING SHE WANTS.

416
00:28:36,100 --> 00:28:37,833
- WHAT'S THE POINT
OF HAVING A DAUGHTER

417
00:28:37,867 --> 00:28:40,367
IF YOU CAN'T SPOIL HER,
RIGHT?

418
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:42,233
- I'M NOT GOING TO
LET YOU TAKE HER.

419
00:28:42,267 --> 00:28:44,267
- WHAT?

420
00:28:44,300 --> 00:28:46,600
- I WON'T LET YOU
TAKE SKYE FROM ME.

421
00:28:48,067 --> 00:28:50,200
- NO--
AAH! AAH! AAH!

422
00:29:20,067 --> 00:29:22,200
- MY MOM'S STILL MAD
ABOUT YESTERDAY.

423
00:29:22,233 --> 00:29:24,467
I SWEAR, ONE MINUTE
SHE'S TREATING ME

424
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:25,767
LIKE I'M ABOUT TO
FALL APART,

425
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:28,067
THE NEXT, LIKE I'M THE WORST KID
IN THE WORLD.

426
00:29:28,067 --> 00:29:30,500
SHE WONDERS WHY I'M IN THERAPY.
[chuckles]

427
00:29:32,567 --> 00:29:34,100
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL,
IT'S JUST--

428
00:29:34,133 --> 00:29:36,467
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO TELL ME
ABOUT IT IF YOU DON'T WANT TO.

429
00:29:36,500 --> 00:29:39,067
- NO, I MEAN,
WHEN I WAS IN JUNIOR HIGH...

430
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:41,733
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO EXPLAIN IT.

431
00:29:41,767 --> 00:29:44,967
THINGS JUST KINDA
FELT LIKE TOO MUCH.

432
00:29:45,067 --> 00:29:47,100
SORTA TRIED TO HURT MYSELF.

433
00:29:49,067 --> 00:29:51,633
I KNOW IT WAS STUPID.
I'M FINE NOW.

434
00:29:55,633 --> 00:29:57,933
WAS THAT TMI?
DID I TOTALLY FREAK YOU OUT?

435
00:30:00,733 --> 00:30:01,767
- NO.

436
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:06,000
TRUST ME, IT TAKES A LOT
TO FREAK ME OUT.

437
00:30:09,933 --> 00:30:13,367
- I ALWAYS WONDERED WHAT IT
WOULD BE LIKE TO HAVE A SISTER.

438
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:16,200
IT'S KINDA COOL.

439
00:30:16,233 --> 00:30:18,300
